.TH "VTTCue.positionAlign" "JS" "April 8, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
VTTCue.positionAlign \- VTTCue: positionAlign property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]positionAlign\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]VTTCue\f[R]
interface is used to determine what \f[CR]VTTCue.position\f[R] is
anchored to.
.SH VALUE
A string containing one of the following values:
.TP
\f[B]\[dq]line\-left\[dq]\f[R]
Line\-left alignment.
.TP
\f[B]\[dq]center\[dq]\f[R]
Center alignment.
.TP
\f[B]\[dq]line\-right\[dq]\f[R]
Line\-right alignment.
.TP
\f[B]\[dq]auto\[dq]\f[R]
Automatic alignment, which depends on the text alignment of the cue,
interpreted as follows:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]line\-left:\f[R] if the text alignment is left, the cue is using a
LTR language and the text alignment is start, or the cue is using a RTL
language and the text alignment is end.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]line\-right:\f[R] if the text alignment is right, the cue is using
a RTL language and the text alignment is start, or the cue is using a
LTR language and the text\-alignment is end.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]center:\f[R] if there is no text alignment position set.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
In the following example a new \f[CR]VTTCue\f[R] is created, then the
value of \f[CR]positionAlign\f[R] is set to
\f[CR]\[dq]line\-right\[dq]\f[R].
The value is then printed to the console.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] video = document.querySelector(\[dq]video\[dq]);
\f[B]let\f[R] track = video.addTextTrack(\[dq]captions\[dq], \[dq]Captions\[dq], \[dq]en\[dq]);
track.mode = \[dq]showing\[dq];

\f[B]let\f[R] cue1 = \f[B]new\f[R] VTTCue(0, 0.9, \[dq]Hildy!\[dq]);
cue1.positionAlign = \[dq]line\-right\[dq];
console.log(cue1.positionAlign);

track.addCue(cue1);
.EE
